import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['age'] = pd.to_numeric(data['age'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['age'].median(), color='red', label='Median Age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the age distribution of the victims?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    race_counts = data['race'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(race_counts, labels=race_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the racial distribution of the victims?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['death_date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['death_date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    type_counts = data['type'].value_counts()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(type_counts.index, type_counts.values)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of the type of incidents?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Type of Incident')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['death_date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['death_date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))
    ax.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], alpha=0.5, color='red')
    plt.title('What is the geographical distribution of the incidents?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
